# Image Build Matrix

Use these scripts to produce four final disk images:

| Target | Final image |
| --- | --- |
| Arch Linux `x86_64` | `artifacts/mutuatechlinux-general-x86_64.img` |
| Arch Linux `aarch64` | `artifacts/mutuatechlinux-general-aarch64.img` |
| CachyOS `x86_64_v3` | `artifacts/mutuatechlinux-general-cachyos-x86_64_v3.img` |
| CachyOS `x86_64_v4` | `artifacts/mutuatechlinux-general-cachyos-x86_64_v4.img` |

## Build, Test, Publish

### Arch Linux `x86_64`

```bash
cd x86_64
sudo ./build_archlinux_x86_64_image
./test_x86_64_image
./publish_x86_64_image
cd initrd_installer
sudo ./generate_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer
./publish_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer
```

### Arch Linux `aarch64`

```bash
cd aarch64
sudo ./build_aarch64_image
./test_image
./publish_aarch64_image
cd initrd_installer
sudo ./generate_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer
./publish_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer
```

### CachyOS `x86_64_v3`

```bash
cd x86_64
sudo ./build_cachyos_v3_image
./test_cachyos_v3_image
./publish_cachyos_v3_image
cd initrd_installer
sudo ./generate_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer
./publish_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer
```

### CachyOS `x86_64_v4`

```bash
cd x86_64
sudo ./build_cachyos_v4_image
./test_cachyos_v4_image
./publish_cachyos_v4_image
cd initrd_installer
sudo ./generate_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer
./publish_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer
```

## Notes

- The Arch `x86_64` and `aarch64` on-site installer generators still exist exactly as before.
- The generic Arch installer entrypoints now use explicit names: `archlinux_x86_64` and `archlinux_aarch64`.
- The generic Arch `x86_64` image builder now uses an explicit name too: `build_archlinux_x86_64_image`.
- The CachyOS `x86_64_v3` and `x86_64_v4` initrd generator wrappers are convenience entrypoints that make the installer fetch the matching CachyOS final image automatically.
- The old generic script names are kept as compatibility wrappers.
- The initrd installer test wrappers create a disposable copy of the built image, replace the boot kernel and initramfs with the generated installer artifacts, optionally wipe everything except `/boot`, and then launch the usual QEMU test flow.
- All publish helpers accept `REMOTE_HOST` and `REMOTE_BASE_DIR` overrides.
- Image publish helpers use `XZ_LEVEL=1` by default; initrd publish helpers use `XZ_LEVEL=9`.
- The `x86_64_v4` builder intentionally aborts on hosts that do not report `x86-64-v4` support.
- The `aarch64` builder still requires `qemu-user-static` plus binfmt support.

## Generic Helpers

These are the shared low-level helpers used by the wrapper scripts:

- `common/publish_image`
- `common/publish_initrd_artifacts`

They can be called directly if you want to override paths manually.
